#1. Data Pre-processing:
#• Load the flight delay dataset.
#• Handle missing values.
#• Provide a statistical summary of the dataset (mean, median, mode, standard deviation, etc.).
#• Understand the shape and structure of the dataset (number of rows/columns,data types).

import pandas as pd

# Load the flight delay dataset with low_memory=False to avoid DtypeWarning

data_types = df.dtypes

# Print the summary statistics, shape, and data types

print(summary)
print("\nShape of the Dataset:")
print(shape)
print("\nData Types of Columns:")
print(data_types)

#2.. Univariate Analysis:
# Plot the distribution for each feature using histograms or density plots.
# If there are categorical variables, showcase the frequency of each category using bar plots.
# Describe any paterns or anomalies you observe from the univariate analysis.


import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Define the data types for specific columns (modify as needed)
dtype_dict = {
    'FLIGHT_NUMBER': int,
    'MONTH': int,
    'DAY': int,
    'DAY_OF_WEEK': int,
    'AIRLINE': str,  # Assuming 'AIRLINE' is the correct column name for airlines
    'ORIGIN_AIRPORT': str,  # Assuming 'ORIGIN_AIRPORT' is the correct column name
    'DESTINATION_AIRPORT': str,  # Assuming 'DESTINATION_AIRPORT' is the correct column name
    'SCHEDULED_DEPARTURE': int,
    'DEPARTURE_TIME': float,
    'SCHEDULED_ARRIVAL': int,
    'ARRIVAL_TIME': float,
    'ARRIVAL_DELAY': float
}

# Load the flight delay dataset with specified data types and low_memory=False
df = pd.read_csv("flightsdata.csv", dtype=dtype_dict, low_memory=False)

# Univariate analysis for numeric features (e.g., MONTH, DAY)
numeric_features = ['MONTH', 'DAY', 'SCHEDULED_DEPARTURE', 'DEPARTURE_TIME', 'SCHEDULED_ARRIVAL', 'ARRIVAL_TIME', 'ARRIVAL_DELAY']

# Plot histograms for numeric features
for feature in numeric_features:
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    plt.hist(df[feature], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.title(f'Distribution of {feature}')
    plt.xlabel(feature)
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.show()

# Univariate analysis for the categorical feature (AIRLINE)
categorical_feature = 'AIRLINE'

# Plot a bar plot to show the frequency of each airline
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
df[categorical_feature].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', color='green', alpha=0.7)
plt.title(f'Frequency of {categorical_feature}')
plt.xlabel(categorical_feature)
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.show()

#3 3. Initial Data Exploration:
#• Check the first few rows to understand the dataset.
#• Get summary statistics for each column.
# Identify the percentage of flights delayed by more than 15 minutes.




import pandas as pd

# Define data types for columns (5 and 6) to avoid DtypeWarning
dtype_dict = {'column5_name': 'object', 'column6_name': 'object'}

# Load the flight delay dataset with specified data types and low_memory=False
df = pd.read_csv("flightsdata.csv", dtype=dtype_dict, low_memory=False)

# Check the first few rows to understand the dataset
print("First few rows of the dataset:")
print(df.head())

# Get summary statistics for each column
summary = df.describe()
print("\nSummary Statistics:")
print(summary)

# Identify the percentage of flights delayed by more than 15 minutes
delayed_flights = df[df['ARRIVAL_DELAY'] > 15]
percentage_delayed = (len(delayed_flights) / len(df)) * 100
print(f"\nPercentage of flights delayed by more than 15 minutes: {percentage_delayed:.2f}%")

#4. Visual Analysis:
#• Visualize the distribution of flight delays.
#• Compare average delays across different airlines.
#• Investigate the impact of the day of the week on delays.
#• Analyze if there's any patern of delays based on the scheduled departure hour.
#• Understand the correlation between the various numeric variables.
#• Check if there's any seasonality in delays.



import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load the flight delay dataset
df = pd.read_csv("flightsdata.csv")

dtype_dict = {'column5_name': str, 'column6_name': str}  # Modify with actual column names and desired data types

# Load the flight delay dataset with specified data types and low_memory=False
df = pd.read_csv("flightsdata.csv", dtype=dtype_dict, low_memory=False)


# Plot the distribution of flight delays
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.histplot(data=df, x="ARRIVAL_DELAY", kde=True)
plt.xlabel("Arrival Delay (minutes)")
plt.ylabel("Frequency")
plt.title("Distribution of Flight Delays")
plt.show()

# Compare average delays across different airlines
average_delays = df.groupby("AIRLINE").agg({"ARRIVAL_DELAY": "mean"}).sort_values(by="ARRIVAL_DELAY", ascending=False)
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.barplot(x=average_delays.index, y=average_delays["ARRIVAL_DELAY"])
plt.xlabel("Airline")
plt.ylabel("Average Arrival Delay (minutes)")
plt.title("Average Arrival Delay by Airline")
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.show()

# Investigate the impact of the day of the week on delays
average_delays_by_day = df.groupby("DAY_OF_WEEK").agg({"ARRIVAL_DELAY": "mean"}).sort_index()
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.lineplot(x=average_delays_by_day.index, y=average_delays_by_day["ARRIVAL_DELAY"])
plt.xlabel("Day of the Week")
plt.ylabel("Average Arrival Delay (minutes)")
plt.title("Average Arrival Delay by Day of the Week")
plt.show()

# Analyze the pattern of delays based on the scheduled departure hour
df["SCHEDULED_DEPARTURE_HOUR"] = df["SCHEDULED_DEPARTURE"] // 100
average_delays_by_hour = df.groupby("SCHEDULED_DEPARTURE_HOUR").agg({"ARRIVAL_DELAY": "mean"}).sort_index()
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.lineplot(x=average_delays_by_hour.index, y=average_delays_by_hour["ARRIVAL_DELAY"])
plt.xlabel("Scheduled Departure Hour")
plt.ylabel("Average Arrival Delay (minutes)")
plt.title("Average Arrival Delay by Scheduled Departure Hour")
plt.show()

# Understand the correlation between the various numeric variables
correlation_matrix = df.corr()
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot=True, cmap="coolwarm", linewidths=0.5)
plt.title("Correlation Heatmap")
plt.show()

# Check if there's any seasonality in delays
average_delays_by_month = df.groupby("MONTH").agg({"ARRIVAL_DELAY": "mean"}).sort_index()
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.lineplot(x=average_delays_by_month.index, y=average_delays_by_month["ARRIVAL_DELAY"])
plt.xlabel("Month")
plt.ylabel("Average Arrival Delay (minutes)")
plt.title("Average Arrival Delay by Month")
plt.show()

#5. Deep Dive Analysis:
#• Identify the origin-destination pairs with the highest average delays.
#• Analyze the 10 most frequent flight routes and their average delays.
#• Visualize the relationship between the origin and destination airports using a heatmap.

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load the flight delay dataset with specified data types
dtype_dict = {'ORIGIN_AIRPORT': str, 'DESTINATION_AIRPORT': str}
df = pd.read_csv("flightsdata.csv", dtype=dtype_dict, low_memory=False)

# Identify the origin-destination pairs with the highest average delays
average_delays_by_route = df.groupby(["ORIGIN_AIRPORT", "DESTINATION_AIRPORT"])["ARRIVAL_DELAY"].mean().sort_values(ascending=False).head(10)

# Convert the MultiIndex to a regular DataFrame
average_delays_by_route = average_delays_by_route.reset_index()

# Create a barplot to visualize the top 10 routes with the highest average delays
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.barplot(data=average_delays_by_route, x="ORIGIN_AIRPORT", y="ARRIVAL_DELAY")
plt.xlabel("Origin-Destination Pair")
plt.ylabel("Average Arrival Delay (minutes)")
plt.title("Top 10 Routes with Highest Average Delays")
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.show()

# Analyze the 10 most frequent flight routes and their average delays
df["Route"] = df["ORIGIN_AIRPORT"] + " to " + df["DESTINATION_AIRPORT"]
top_10_frequent_routes = df["Route"].value_counts().head(10).index
average_delays_frequent_routes = df[df["Route"].isin(top_10_frequent_routes)].groupby("Route")["ARRIVAL_DELAY"].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)

# Create a barplot to visualize the average delays for the top 10 most frequent flight routes
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.barplot(y=average_delays_frequent_routes.index, x=average_delays_frequent_routes.values)
plt.xlabel("Average Arrival Delay (minutes)")
plt.ylabel("Route")
plt.title("Top 10 Most Frequent Flight Routes and Their Average Delays")
plt.show()

# Visualize the relationship between the origin and destination airports using a heatmap
airport_corr = df.groupby(["ORIGIN_AIRPORT", "DESTINATION_AIRPORT"])["ARRIVAL_DELAY"].mean().unstack()
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
sns.heatmap(airport_corr, cmap="YlGnBu", annot=True, fmt=".1f")
plt.xlabel("Destination Airport")
plt.ylabel("Origin Airport")
plt.title("Average Arrival Delays Heatmap by Origin-Destination Pairs")
plt.show()
